.TH CORTEX-AI 1 "2026-03-27" "cortex-ai 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cortex-ai \- Command-line tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cortex-ai
[
B-h
    R | 
        B--help
               R]
.br
.B cortex-ai

ICOMMAND
        R [
           ISUBCOMMAND
                      R] [
                          IARGS
                               R...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cortex-ai
.SH COMMANDS
Available commands:
.TP
.B recommend
Show intelligent agent recommendations
.TP
.B auto-activate
Auto-activate high-confidence recommendations
.TP
.B export
Export recommendations to JSON
.TP
.B record-success
Record current session as successful for learning
.TP
.B ingest-review
Ingest specialist review into skill learning
.TP
.B watch
Watch mode - real-time monitoring and recommendations
.TP
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help message and exit
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT
Override for context directory (set automatically by Claude Code when running plugin commands)
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.claude/
Default context directory containing agents, modes, rules, and other configuration
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cortex-ai-tui (1),
.BR cortex-ai-workflow (1)
